On 2/3/2019, a Shiite crowd protested in Manama's Bilad al Qadim suburb against a Bahraini court sentencing 167 Shiites to 1 to 10 years in prison for holding a sit-in that continued for several months outside the house of Ayatollah Sheikh Qassim after the regime revoked his citizenship. The protesters also chanted slogans against Bahrain's top court decision to upheld the death penalty for two Shiite men in connection with a fatal bombing in which two policemen were killed in Sitrah in 2015, and the death sentence for four Shiite men over an explosion that killed a security officer in Diraz in 2017. [size=dozens]
